-frame-17","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#features","content":"**React Aria integration**: Uses Provider pattern so nested elements stay in sync with the frame"},"165":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-18","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#features","content":"**Field wrapper composition**: Designed to sit inside TextField, NumberField, DateField, or Select as the main field UI"},"166":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-19","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#props","content":"FieldFrame accepts the following props:"},"167":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-20","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#basic-example","content":"Examples for leading control, trailing control, and icon accessories are in Examples at the end."},"168":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-21","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"FieldFrame renders a single React Aria `Provider` that supplies the necessary context to its children. Structure tree:"},"169":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-22","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"The following list describes the internal React Aria components used to compose FieldFrame:"},"170":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-23","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"**Label** (optional) — Rendered when `label` is provided. Shows a required indicator (asterisk)."},"171":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-24","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"**Group** — The visual frame. Exposes `data-focus-within`, `data-focus-visible`, `data-disabled`, and `data-invalid`. All focusable children (input, button, etc.) live inside this Group."},"172":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-25","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"**FieldError** (optional) — Rendered when `errorMessage` is provided. Rendered below the Group, above the description. Associated with the field for accessibility."},"173":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-26","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"**Text** (optional) — Description block rendered when `description` is provided."},"174":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-27","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"Children you pass to FieldFrame (e.g. `Input`, `Button`, `DateInput`, `SelectValue`) are rendered inside the Group. The provider ensures nested Input and Button read the same disabled/required state as the frame."},"175":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-28","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#states","content":"The states **disabled**, **readonly**, and **invalid** are applied when the field wrapper (e.g. TextField, NumberField, Select) is marked as disabled, readonly, or invalid respectively. The frame reflects these and other states via data attributes on the group."},"176":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-29","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#states","content":"State"},"177":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-30","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#states","content":"CSS Selector"},"